==Old English==

===Etymology===
An early Germanic borrowing from Latin [[angelus]], from Greek [[ἄγγελος|αγγελος]] ‘messenger’. Cognate with Old Frisian ''engel'', Old Saxon [[engil]] (Dutch ''engel''), Old High German [[engil]] (German [[Engel]]), Old Norse [[engill]] (Swedish [[ängel]]). (Gothic [[𐌰𐌲𐌲𐌹𐌻𐌿𐍃]] was apparently borrowed immediately from the Greek.)

